The paper deals with coding theory, specifically with the generalization of Gabidulin codes to infinite fields and integer rings. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses decoding algorithms and error correction, which are relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of side information and reduction of decoding problems to finite fields also relates to statistical learning (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
